9
00:00:23,220 --> 00:00:26,100
♫Where’s that love people are saying?♫

10
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:29,500
♫To always be by each other’s sides♫

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:32,580
♫The love that’s willing to sacrifice everything♫

12
00:00:32,580 --> 00:00:35,580
♫Everything even my own life♫

13
00:00:35,580 --> 00:00:39,060
♫Do they really exist? I’d rather not believe it♫

14
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:42,140
♫I don’t think I’ll ever fall for anyone♫

15
00:00:42,140 --> 00:00:45,380
♫Love? I don’t find it interesting♫

16
00:00:45,380 --> 00:00:48,460
♫Sorry about that♫

17
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:51,500
♫But then who are you?♫

18
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,500
♫To make my heart keep fluttering♫

19
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,900
♫Please tell me♫

20
00:00:58,140 --> 00:01:01,220
♫What’s happening with my heart?♫

21
00:01:01,220 --> 00:01:04,580
♫It can’t be, why am I feeling this?♫

22
00:01:04,580 --> 00:01:07,660
♫Oh, my heart is pounding so fast♫

23
00:01:07,660 --> 00:01:10,740
♫Time freezes whenever I see you♫

24
00:01:10,740 --> 00:01:14,100
♫I wonder why every time you smile♫

25
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:17,380
♫Something in your eyes make me go weak♫

26
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,580
♫Oh no, this is real–it’s not a dream♫

27
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:23,460
♫Or is the love that people are saying...♫

28
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:25,340
♫Is it you?♫

29
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:32,060
♫Is it you?♫

30
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:35,620
[Flaming Chains of Love]

31
00:01:35,860 --> 00:01:38,930
[Previously]
This is Mum’s house. You’re not allowed to bring your new lover here.

32
00:01:39,130 --> 00:01:42,050
I’ve never said I’ll bring my new lover here.

33
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:43,810
If not a lover, then who the hell is she?

34
00:01:44,060 --> 00:01:47,050
Long time no see, Buffalo Fai.

35
00:01:47,259 --> 00:01:50,210
What if one day, she tries to seduce him for his money?

36
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:51,810
Over my dead body then.

37
00:01:51,810 --> 00:01:55,710
I’m going to help you at work–but only on one condition.

38
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:57,979
You have to let Kaphrao be my assistant.

39
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:58,800
Deal.

40
00:01:59,410 --> 00:02:04,910
From now on, you have to do whatever I say because I’m now officially your boss.

41
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:08,110
I can’t believe you’re really teaching me some work.

42
00:02:08,130 --> 00:02:11,150
The dump truck tickets are with Uncle Yod. Can you go get them for me?

43
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,000
Get them from where?

44
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,100
Behind that mountain over there.

45
00:02:13,260 --> 00:02:14,360
How do you expect me to go there?

46
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:15,560
Probably by feet.

47
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:19,850
Walk? Are you crazy? It’s freaking hot and far.

48
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:25,150
Please. Think of it as your first assignment.

49
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,050
But it’s hot as hell!

50
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:37,050
Slacking off right on your first day–Dad really overrated you.

51
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:49,500
So?

52
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:22,480
Make the whole ground flat so it’d be easier for us to get the stones up there

53
00:03:23,410 --> 00:03:24,930
and bring them down here.

54
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,550
Uncle Yod!

55
00:03:27,660 --> 00:03:29,480
Oh! Miss Kaphrao!

56
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,680
What are you doing here? It’s dangerous.

57
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:36,550
Fai told me to get the dump truck tickets from you.

58
00:03:37,130 --> 00:03:38,950
I already gave them to her.

59
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:39,780
What?

60
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:43,660
But she said she doesn’t have them.

61
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:47,180
Here, look. I already sent them.

62
00:03:48,110 --> 00:03:49,180
You did?

63
00:03:50,710 --> 00:03:53,510
Why the heck did she tell me to come here then?

64
00:04:02,980 --> 00:04:04,080
That jerk!

65
00:04:15,650 --> 00:04:20,279
Oops, sorry. They’re here.

66
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:23,380
I totally forgot he already sent me.

67
00:04:23,780 --> 00:04:26,180
I wanted to call but I don’t have your number.

68
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:29,180
Never mind.

69
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:35,010
But thanks anyway. Look at your face–so greasy.

70
00:04:36,930 --> 00:04:39,980
Is there anything you want me to do, Miss Buffalo Fai?

71
00:04:41,810 --> 00:04:44,310
Hmm, let me think.

72
00:05:00,530 --> 00:05:03,410
Can you count the rocks in these two piles?

73
00:05:03,410 --> 00:05:04,780
Our client wants to know the amount.

74
00:05:09,530 --> 00:05:11,580
Is that how you usually do it?

75
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:14,410
Yes, if it’s not a big purchase.

76
00:05:15,460 --> 00:05:16,810
You sell it by piece?

77
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:19,710
Yes, we sell in retail too.

78
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:28,250
You keep finding excuses because you don’t want to do it, don't you?

79
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:32,250
It’s just your first day and you’re getting lazy already. I’m going to tell Dad.

80
00:05:33,530 --> 00:05:34,850
Fine!

81
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:30,980
Hang on, Miss Phrao. What are you doing?

82
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,580
I’m counting rocks.

83
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:36,950
Counting rocks? That’s not how we do it.

84
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,909
We sell them by tons, not by pieces.

85
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,150
What?

86
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:42,780
Look there. See that?

87
00:06:44,659 --> 00:06:48,010
They’ll scoop up the whole pile onto the dump truck and weigh them. That’s it.

88
00:06:48,010 --> 00:06:50,580
That’s it…

89
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,700
That’s it?

90
00:07:00,130 --> 00:07:03,080
That’s how we do it if it’s not a big purchase.

91
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:04,750
We sell in retail too.

92
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,450
Buffalo Fai!

93
00:07:14,530 --> 00:07:16,180
You must be exhausted today.

94
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:21,610
Yes, but I’ve learnt a lot of things.

95
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,580
Thank you so much indeed.

96
00:07:27,330 --> 00:07:28,410
No problem.

97
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,550
Please let me drive.

98
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:36,380
You’re the boss. It’s me who should be the driver.

99
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:38,610
Come, just sit back and relax.

100
00:07:38,610 --> 00:07:39,930
It’s okay, I can drive.

101
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:43,280
It’s all right. You’ve been working all day.

102
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:46,850
There, go on.

103
00:07:56,180 --> 00:07:57,100
Buffalo Fai!

104
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,330
Can’t you go faster?

105
00:08:21,860 --> 00:08:23,550
The turtle is probably biting on our tyre now.

106
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,480
Well, I’m sleepy.

107
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:37,809
I was out in the sun and did the labour work all day.

108
00:08:37,809 --> 00:08:39,549
But don’t worry though.

109
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,910
I’m okay. I can drive.

110
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:50,110
Look at yourself first. Are you sure we’ll get home today?

111
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,330
Come and drive it yourself then.

112
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:55,100
So ungrateful.

113
00:08:55,930 --> 00:08:59,180
Why is she sulking?

114
00:09:21,530 --> 00:09:22,780
Hey!

115
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,710
I know what you’re thinking, you silly Gremlin.

116
00:09:26,710 --> 00:09:29,150
You wanted to trick me to get out of the car and left me here, didn’t you?

117
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:33,380
No! All you can think of is finding a way to get back at me!

118
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,480
Aren’t you like that too?

119
00:09:36,130 --> 00:09:37,150
No, I’m not!

120
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:42,180
How did she know?

121
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:50,010
Hey! Let me get in! Hey!

122
00:09:50,010 --> 00:09:53,880
Do you hear me? Hey! Let me get in!

123
00:09:57,700 --> 00:10:00,980
Unlock the door! Let me get in! Hey!

124
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,850
Apologise first.

125
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,350
For what?

126
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,310
For trying to trick me earlier.

127
00:10:07,330 --> 00:10:08,580
Why did you pick on me–

128
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:10,080
There! You just admit it.

129
00:10:12,130 --> 00:10:14,410
Stay outside then.

130
00:10:14,730 --> 00:10:16,150
It’s a bit hot though.

131
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:27,680
Fine! Sorry, Fai!

132
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:33,210
Say it nicely and politely–”I’m sorry, Miss Fai.”

133
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:39,210
Are you going to say it? Fine, not saying it, huh?

134
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:43,710
Okay, okay! I’ll say it! Let me get in!

135
00:10:45,860 --> 00:10:47,980
I’m sorry, Miss Fai!

136
00:10:49,660 --> 00:10:50,880
Can’t hear you.

137
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:55,150
I’m sorry, Miss Fai!

138
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:04,280
Dad said you used to take a dance class and did quite well too. Show me a bit then.

139
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:05,910
You’re going too far!

140
00:11:07,130 --> 00:11:10,010
Or do you want to walk back? It’s hot though.

141
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:12,150
Boiling hot.

142
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:16,380
Come on, show me.

143
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,930
I’ll film it too.

144
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:23,080
The view in the background is just perfect.

145
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:26,380
I’ll save the clip to recheck later if you’re doing it right.

146
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:27,710
Just you wait.

147
00:11:28,210 --> 00:11:30,410
Don’t let me wait too long then.

148
00:11:30,410 --> 00:11:32,980
Hurry up. It’s hot.

149
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:35,410
Let’s go!

150
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:37,680
That’s it? Is that all they taught you?

151
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:38,610
Yeah.

152
00:11:39,530 --> 00:11:41,050
Make it stronger.

153
00:11:43,330 --> 00:11:47,210
Step back a little. I need a full-body view for the clip.

154
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:49,150
Just you wait!

155
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,780
Make it cute, can’t you? That’s not cute.

156
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,580
Come and do it yourself then!

157
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:00,710
Enough?

158
00:12:00,710 --> 00:12:01,710
More.

159
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:07,150
Make it stronger. An old lady next door can even do better.

160
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,480
Geez, you!

161
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,850
Wanna walk back?

162
00:12:11,060 --> 00:12:12,260
What? Tired already?

163
00:12:14,930 --> 00:12:17,180
Yeah, that’s right. See? You can actually do it

164
00:12:38,910 --> 00:12:42,210
Sorry, my dad’s probably gone to bed by now.

165
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:45,610
I don’t think you can complain about me today.

166
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,780
Look, I’m all grown up.

167
00:12:49,780 --> 00:12:52,380
I’m not gonna waste my time doing something nonsense like that.

168
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:56,950
Don’t forget to shower when you get home.

169
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:00,560
You’re stinking so bad I almost gag.

170
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,800
The scent is still there.

171
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:11,680
Stinking? Smell it then!

172
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:12,680
Smell it! Go on!

173
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:16,580
- Smelly Guinea Pig!
- Eat this!

174
00:13:18,180 --> 00:13:20,010
Get off me! That’s gross!

175
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:23,780
Come here, baby! Why are you running away?

176
00:13:23,780 --> 00:13:27,310
Geez, stinky, huh?

177
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:30,350
Yuck! I really stink.

178
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:32,210
I’m having goosebumps, brrr!

179
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:46,850
Fai, why are you back so late, dear. I’ve been waiting to eat with you.

180
00:13:48,130 --> 00:13:52,310
I’m sorry, Auntie. I forgot to call that I’d be late.

181
00:13:52,310 --> 00:13:54,550
There was a little problem on our way back.

182
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:57,310
Has Kaphrao caused you any trouble?

183
00:13:58,330 --> 00:13:59,380
Not at all.

184
00:14:00,060 --> 00:14:05,510
If that girl ever does anything to upset you, you can always tell me. I’ll go deal with her.

185
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:12,880
It’s all right, Auntie, I can handle it. I’m a big girl now. I won’t let anyone pick on me so easily.

186
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:17,700
Actually, Ak has so many businesses.

187
00:14:18,060 --> 00:14:20,710
Why does he have to send Kaphrao to work here?

188
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:22,950
And even work with you.

189
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,810
I really don’t know what he’s thinking.

190
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:29,310
But isn’t it better to keep her here?

191
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:30,880
How?

192
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:36,310
So that she’ll always be in our sight.

193
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:42,000
If Dad had sent her to live outside, we wouldn’t have known when he went to see her or do anything with her.

194
00:14:43,660 --> 00:14:47,810
I’ve never liked this girl, from the very first moment.

195
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:54,350
When you were still under my care, I had never once raised my hand to you.

196
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:59,910
But when Ak brought this girl into the house, everyday was troublesome.

197
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:04,680
Ak always punished you, my dear.

198
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:12,980
He never once raised a hand to that Gremlin. Whatever she did just pleased him.

199
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:19,380
Unlike me, whatever I did was wrong in his eyes.

200
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:27,110
I’m always on your side, dear.

201
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:37,060
There’s only you who loves me the most.

202
00:15:41,130 --> 00:15:45,880
But don’t worry, that girl won’t be here for long.

203
00:15:49,330 --> 00:15:50,600
Let’s eat.

204
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:56,450
Eat up. They’re all your favourites.

205
00:15:56,450 --> 00:15:57,260
Thank you.

206
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,580
Throw it away.

207
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:10,560
Yes, Young Master.

208
00:16:11,130 --> 00:16:12,710
Hey, hold on!

209
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:13,880
Stop!

210
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:17,110
What are you doing with my bike?

211
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:18,850
Throwing it away.

212
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,910
Didn’t my dad give it to you?

213
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:23,550
That means you didn’t own it in the first place.

214
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:26,350
Are you nuts? It’s still in good condition, why would you throw it away?

215
00:16:26,930 --> 00:16:28,110
Piak, throw it away!

216
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:29,910
But, Young Master–

217
00:16:29,910 --> 00:16:30,780
Piak!

218
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:32,280
Yes, Young Master.

219
00:16:34,810 --> 00:16:35,760
You!

220
00:16:36,660 --> 00:16:37,800
Are you having fun?

221
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,100
Absolutely.

222
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:40,450
Maniac!

223
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:46,880
But if you give up and beg me nicely, I might consider giving you a ride.

224
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:49,080
You need to work at the office today, don’t you?

225
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:53,880
No need. I have legs, I can walk.

226
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:57,200
But it’s far, are you sure you can walk there?

227
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:58,880
It’s better than going with you!

228
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:20,579
These are accounting records from previous years. Young Master said you must go through all of them.

229
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:21,760
All of them–

230
00:17:22,730 --> 00:17:24,980
Geez, her manners.

231
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:33,510
Young Master said you can’t go home if you don’t finish it today.

232
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,810
Sure, this is nothing.

233
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:39,350
I’ll definitely get it done today.

234
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:45,460
That’s not all.

235
00:17:45,860 --> 00:17:49,510
Here are records of every main and subsidiary business that the Master owns.

236
00:17:50,530 --> 00:17:51,330
Yes?

237
00:17:53,060 --> 00:17:56,710
Young Master said if you think you can’t do it…

238
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:02,250
Then come and beg me. I’ll be waiting upstairs.

239
00:18:09,130 --> 00:18:14,280
Go tell your Young Master that this is a piece of cake for me.

240
00:18:14,910 --> 00:18:16,050
Bullsh*t.

241
00:18:17,150 --> 00:18:19,680
Geez, just like her boss.

242
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:48,780
I heard that day when you took her to the mine, you made her count rocks and do the labour work under the sun.

243
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:53,210
I just want to help her practise patience.

244
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:55,610
Practise patience?

245
00:18:56,710 --> 00:19:00,380
By throwing her bike away and letting her walk to work,

246
00:19:00,380 --> 00:19:03,710
and even make her work until late at night?

247
00:19:04,150 --> 00:19:06,410
Are you sure you’re not picking on her again?

248
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:11,410
Did that Gremlin rat me out again?

249
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:14,380
It doesn’t matter who told me.

250
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:19,350
I left her in your care because I wanted you to train her at work–

251
00:19:20,310 --> 00:19:22,610
not to use her as your emotional dumpster.

252
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:28,510
Is that all you have to say to me?

253
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:38,510
I’m warning you, you should know when to stop.

254
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:44,080
What if anything happens to her again like that time, what will you do?

255
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,580
You still remember it, right?

256
00:19:49,660 --> 00:19:51,950
So what? I don’t care.

257
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:25,910
Huh, Miss Phrao?

258
00:20:27,660 --> 00:20:29,180
You’re still here?

259
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:32,450
I’m still not done. There’s a lot more to do.

260
00:20:32,730 --> 00:20:34,910
Are you here to close up the office?

261
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:40,950
Yes. Why don’t you just leave it for tomorrow?

262
00:20:41,350 --> 00:20:43,280
It’s dangerous to walk home alone this late.

263
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:45,050
I’ll give you a ride.

264
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:50,310
It’s all right. Judging from the amount of work, I guess I’ll have to pull an all-nighter.

265
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:55,250
Well then, are you sure?

266
00:20:55,530 --> 00:20:56,330
Yes.

267
00:20:59,330 --> 00:21:02,880
Then, please lock the back door for me when you leave.

268
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,850
Oh, sure.

269
00:21:05,530 --> 00:21:07,280
I'm leaving now.

270
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:08,100
Goodnight.

271
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,550
She’s still working?

272
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:28,150
Yes, are you sure you’re going to leave her there alone?

273
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,810
It’s dark and deserted around there at night.

274
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:35,580
She wants to stay there herself. It’s not like I’ve forced her.

275
00:21:36,850 --> 00:21:39,180
But she doesn’t have her bike with her.

276
00:21:39,180 --> 00:21:41,610
And it looks like it’s going to rain too.

277
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:48,280
If you’re worried this much, why don’t you just drop her home?

278
00:21:48,660 --> 00:21:52,280
I already offered but she refused to go home.

279
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:56,480
If she’s so stubborn, just leave her be.

280
00:21:56,910 --> 00:21:57,980
I’m hanging up.

281
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:16,650
Fai, is everything okay? I saw you came back a while ago.

282
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:20,350
Who were you talking to on the phone?

283
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,680
I was discussing work with Uncle Yod.

284
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:27,080
It’s late, why aren’t you in bed yet, Auntie?

285
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:31,310
I was about to turn in but I’m waiting for you to come home first.

286
00:22:32,330 --> 00:22:38,710
We might have a good dream tonight. Looks like it’s going to rain. It’s been pretty cloudy since evening.

287
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,210
Let’s go, dear.

288
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:44,150
I’ve been knitting all day long.

289
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:46,580
Then, let’s get some sleep.

290
00:22:47,130 --> 00:22:48,880
So that we’ll have a good dream.

291
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:49,960
Okay then.

292
00:22:53,130 --> 00:22:54,710
Sweet dream, Auntie.

293
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,500
I’ll shower and go to bed too.

294
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,400
Yes, dear.

295
00:23:43,130 --> 00:23:46,250
[Yod]: Are you sure you’re going to leave Miss Phrao there alone, Young Master?

296
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:49,080
It’s dark and deserted around there at night.

297
00:23:49,810 --> 00:23:51,550
She doesn’t have her bike with her.

298
00:23:51,550 --> 00:23:54,250
And it looks like it’s going to rain too.

299
00:23:56,960 --> 00:24:01,150
[Akanee]: I’m warning you, you should know when to stop.

300
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:05,450
What if anything happens to her again like that time, what will you do?

301
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,110
You still remember, right?

302
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:59,710
Can’t you just give in for once? You silly Gremlin.

303
00:25:52,660 --> 00:25:55,510
Does she want to die buried under a pile of work for real?

304
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,580
Geez, why now?

305
00:26:44,730 --> 00:26:45,950
Panel board…

306
00:27:40,980 --> 00:27:41,650
Boo!

307
00:27:42,010 --> 00:27:42,810
Sh*t!

308
00:27:48,150 --> 00:27:49,410
Fai!

309
00:27:54,330 --> 00:27:58,750
Damn it, I’m bleeding.

310
00:28:13,500 --> 00:28:14,710
What’s so funny?

311
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:17,660
If my face is ruined, I’ll kill you.

312
00:28:19,330 --> 00:28:21,510
Who told you to pull a prank on me then?

313
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:24,310
I got startled and had to protect myself.

314
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:35,880
Can’t you be more gentle? Try to behave more like a lady.

315
00:28:36,260 --> 00:28:40,510
Serve you right. If you don’t like it, then just do it yourself.

316
00:28:41,100 --> 00:28:41,900
No.

317
00:28:44,300 --> 00:28:47,700
You’re the cause so you must take responsibility.

318
00:29:20,930 --> 00:29:22,210
Stop whining.

319
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:51,980
Stay still.

320
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:20,910
Did you do that on purpose to get back at me?

321
00:30:22,360 --> 00:30:27,880
Think whatever you want. I’d rather not cast my pearls before swine.

322
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:31,650
Hey! Did you just call me a pig?

323
00:30:37,860 --> 00:30:40,450
You have to be the last to laugh every time, huh?

324
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:43,050
It’s you who’re like that.

325
00:30:43,100 --> 00:30:46,580
You were like that when you were young, and you’ve never changed at all.

326
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:51,210
Who would be like you? You’ve grown up and become another person completely.

327
00:30:52,460 --> 00:30:53,350
How?

328
00:30:55,300 --> 00:30:59,410
When you were little, you were so weak and kept crying all the time.

329
00:30:59,780 --> 00:31:02,680
You clung on to me all the time, it was so annoying.

330
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:11,610
Get off me.

331
00:31:11,610 --> 00:31:14,380
No, I’m scared.

332
00:31:14,930 --> 00:31:18,950
Don’t you want a doll? I’m taking you to get your doll.

333
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:22,150
I don’t want it anymore. I’m scared.

334
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:26,200
If you don’t stop crying, I’ll leave you here alone.

335
00:31:27,460 --> 00:31:29,810
Fai, don’t leave me!

336
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:39,530
Fai!

337
00:31:41,660 --> 00:31:45,680
Did you take her to play outside again? It’s late.

338
00:31:46,530 --> 00:31:49,510
No, Dad. I just took her to see–

339
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:54,510
Then, why is she crying?

340
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:58,680
I told you not to pick on your sister. Haven’t I told you so many times already?

341
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:02,280
But Dad, I didn’t do anything to her!

342
00:32:02,560 --> 00:32:04,610
Don’t you dare lie to my face!

343
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:11,150
If you do it again, I’ll punish you. Consider it a warning.

344
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:13,600
Are you all right, sweetie?

345
00:32:17,060 --> 00:32:20,180
I’ll take you to bed. It’s okay, now.

346
00:32:21,960 --> 00:32:25,910
Don’t be scared, dear.

347
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:36,150
You were a crybaby–crying over every little thing.

348
00:32:36,150 --> 00:32:38,310
That’s why I got scolded off by my dad all the time.

349
00:32:38,680 --> 00:32:41,980
But look at you now, kicking and punching like a thug.

350
00:32:41,980 --> 00:32:44,910
And even love to use your fists to fix problems.

351
00:32:45,660 --> 00:32:48,080
People do change over time.

352
00:32:48,330 --> 00:32:52,110
Who would’ve been consistently awful like you?

353
00:32:57,100 --> 00:33:01,100
That’s why I really want to know–what made you change this much?

354
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:06,650
It’s you.

355
00:33:37,060 --> 00:33:38,150
Kaphrao.

356
00:33:40,800 --> 00:33:45,350
Is it because I’m weak? Is that why Big Sis always picks on me?

357
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:54,880
From now on, I’ll be strong. I’ll never let Big Sis do that to me again.

358
00:33:56,760 --> 00:33:57,910
Yes, sweetie.

359
00:34:03,700 --> 00:34:05,480
You have to be strong.

360
00:34:16,659 --> 00:34:18,150
You must be strong.

361
00:34:39,130 --> 00:34:43,580
All the documents are correct. We’ll show you to your room in a moment.

362
00:34:44,300 --> 00:34:45,100
Thank you.

363
00:34:59,050 --> 00:35:01,710
You’ll be staying here from now on.

364
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:08,550
They’ll teach you to be strong and look after yourself.

365
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:12,680
But there isn’t Uncle or Big Sis here.

366
00:35:14,330 --> 00:35:19,410
You must be a good girl and study hard for your future.

367
00:35:20,530 --> 00:35:25,350
I’ll come visit you every weekend, I promise.

368
00:35:25,930 --> 00:35:33,580
Once you graduate and are big enough to handle her, I’ll come take you home.

369
00:35:35,060 --> 00:35:36,650
Be a good girl, sweetie.

370
00:35:58,360 --> 00:36:04,410
Finally, I can bring you back home.

371
00:36:08,330 --> 00:36:14,210
Don’t worry, I’ll take the best care of her.

372
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:20,480
Kaphrao.

373
00:36:37,060 --> 00:36:39,750
I’ll go there early to finish off the work tomorrow.

374
00:36:41,260 --> 00:36:43,050
Forget it, you don’t need to do it anymore.

375
00:36:43,160 --> 00:36:46,850
Huh? But Miss Duangnate said it’s your order.

376
00:36:47,460 --> 00:36:51,780
And I’m giving you an order now, can’t you understand human language, Guinea Pig?

377
00:36:52,900 --> 00:36:54,000
Fine! I get it.

378
00:36:58,160 --> 00:36:59,310
Wait.

379
00:36:59,460 --> 00:37:01,410
What now? Are you going to pick on me again?

380
00:37:08,350 --> 00:37:09,250
Here.

381
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,550
Does it have holes?

382
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:17,710
No, hurry up and get out.

383
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:50,780
Huh? No holes indeed.

384
00:37:52,330 --> 00:37:56,680
Did I punch her too hard her brain has fallen out? Why so kind all of a sudden?

385
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:08,250
Yeah, yeah, I get it!

386
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:43,600
Fai.

387
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:48,560
It’s pouring outside, where did you rush off to, dear?

388
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:53,980
Oh, I left something at the office so I just went there to get it.

389
00:38:53,980 --> 00:38:57,750
I thought you were already in bed, Auntie.

390
00:38:57,930 --> 00:38:59,860
Well, I heard your car leaving.

391
00:39:01,860 --> 00:39:03,450
Let’s go to bed then.

392
00:39:03,450 --> 00:39:08,280
Hold on, what happened to your lips?

393
00:39:09,400 --> 00:39:13,550
Oh, I wasn’t looking and walked into the door at the office.

394
00:39:14,330 --> 00:39:17,610
But judging from the wound, it doesn’t look that way.

395
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:20,580
I really bumped into the door, Auntie.

396
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:24,010
Come on, let’s go to bed. I’m sleepy now.

397
00:39:24,500 --> 00:39:27,080
Be more careful next time, dear.

398
00:39:27,100 --> 00:39:29,000
Okay, I’ll be more careful.

399
00:39:29,010 --> 00:39:31,350
I’ll apply some cream for you.

400
00:39:39,530 --> 00:39:41,280
Was that a hand or an elephant's foot?

401
00:39:44,930 --> 00:39:45,730
Boo!

402
00:39:46,260 --> 00:39:47,060
Sh*t!

403
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:50,380
My lips are bleeding.

404
00:39:59,130 --> 00:40:01,530
She probably ran to tell Miss Panee everything by now.

405
00:40:06,860 --> 00:40:09,150
Her lips must be swollen so bad.

406
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:23,980
All right guys, I’m going to start now.

407
00:40:23,980 --> 00:40:28,610
This one is a flared skirt with floral print. It’s for 50 baht only!

408
00:40:28,610 --> 00:40:31,080
Oh! Mr. Kittisak just confirmed it.

409
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:34,510
Thank you so much. What? You want to buy it for your girlfriend?

410
00:40:34,510 --> 00:40:38,550
Aww, so romantic! It’s yours now!

411
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:46,650
And here, I proudly present this one. They were what I wore when I got drunk with Princess Blew of Madelin.

412
00:40:46,650 --> 00:40:49,310
I’ll sell them for only 300 baht.

413
00:40:49,310 --> 00:40:54,150
Hang on, let’s make it 500 then–500 baht!

414
00:40:55,900 --> 00:40:56,800
Sorry, Bua.

415
00:40:56,930 --> 00:41:02,580
It’s all right. Guys, I’ll just take a little break first.

416
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:05,650
Miss Phrao.

417
00:41:06,050 --> 00:41:07,710
What are you doing?

418
00:41:08,410 --> 00:41:11,300
I’m selling my clothes on livestream for extra income.

419
00:41:11,560 --> 00:41:12,780
I see.

420
00:41:14,530 --> 00:41:18,300
By the way, why are you up so early today? Are you heading out to work now?

421
00:41:19,130 --> 00:41:21,450
I need to walk there so I have to leave a bit early.

422
00:41:21,460 --> 00:41:24,200
Why don’t you use my bike then?

423
00:41:24,460 --> 00:41:29,150
I’d rather not do that. If Fai finds out, you might be in trouble.

424
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:32,480
You’re right.

425
00:41:32,810 --> 00:41:37,550
Young Master is so mean to you. She’s never been this harsh to other workers.

426
00:41:37,550 --> 00:41:42,010
Usually, she’s very kind–not someone unreasonable like this.

427
00:41:42,010 --> 00:41:45,950
I think she’s probably misunderstood something about you.

428
00:41:46,760 --> 00:41:49,050
So pretty. Is it pricey?

429
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:50,350
Only 50 baht.

430
00:41:51,560 --> 00:41:55,310
I’m used to it. When we were just kids, she was always like this too.

431
00:41:55,310 --> 00:41:59,480
No matter what I did was wrong. Just the fact that I’m breathing is already wrong.

432
00:42:01,260 --> 00:42:05,380
But I’m sure Young Master will finally understand it one day.

433
00:42:05,660 --> 00:42:06,460
Trust me.

434
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:13,010
She’s narrow-minded, self-absorbed, and pigheaded like a frog in the well. She’d never understand anything, Bua.

435
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:14,010
Who are you calling pigheaded?

436
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:21,250
I gotta go.

437
00:42:21,930 --> 00:42:22,730
Okay.

438
00:42:23,130 --> 00:42:24,810
Hey! Wait!

439
00:42:32,760 --> 00:42:37,180
I’m back, guys. Let’s continue, shall we?

440
00:42:37,180 --> 00:42:38,980
I said it’s for 500 earlier, right?

441
00:42:38,980 --> 00:42:42,750
But since I’m quite moody now, let’s make it 1,000 then.

442
00:42:54,500 --> 00:42:56,050
Guinea Pig, get in the car.

443
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:57,960
No need. I can walk.

444
00:43:01,330 --> 00:43:03,610
We’re going to work somewhere else today.

445
00:43:03,730 --> 00:43:04,710
Where then?

446
00:43:05,260 --> 00:43:06,580
Don’t ask. Just get in the car.

447
00:43:06,600 --> 00:43:07,880
Of course, I have to ask.

448
00:43:07,880 --> 00:43:10,180
What if you plan to sell me out or murder me?

449
00:43:10,180 --> 00:43:12,250
I need to be sure someone will find my body.

450
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:14,080
You’re being delulu.

451
00:43:14,100 --> 00:43:15,710
And you can’t be trusted.

452
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:20,010
Get in the car! That’s an order and it’s during working hours now.

453
00:43:20,010 --> 00:43:22,580
You have to do as I say, understood?

454
00:43:23,150 --> 00:43:24,080
Get in!

455
00:43:29,530 --> 00:43:30,550
Fine!

456
00:43:37,160 --> 00:43:39,850
Uncle Yod, I’m going outside with Fai.

457
00:43:39,850 --> 00:43:45,050
If I’m not back within three hours, please tell Uncle and report it to the police.

458
00:44:18,300 --> 00:44:19,810
What are you looking at?

459
00:44:20,110 --> 00:44:21,200
Nothing.

460
00:44:22,100 --> 00:44:23,350
Why did you stare at me?

461
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:30,650
The wound is almost healed. It’s barely visible now.

462
00:44:31,300 --> 00:44:33,550
It shouldn’t have been there in the first place.

463
00:44:33,900 --> 00:44:35,930
You were being childish with that stupid prank first.

464
00:44:36,330 --> 00:44:38,710
You still have the nerve to blame it on someone else?

465
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:50,450
Use this, so it’ll heal faster.

466
00:45:35,200 --> 00:45:38,680
Hey, do we have to meet the client here?

467
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:40,760
No.

468
00:45:41,330 --> 00:45:42,760
Then, why are you taking me here?

469
00:45:43,100 --> 00:45:45,350
I thought you said we’ll be working out of the office today.

470
00:45:45,530 --> 00:45:47,950
Can you stop asking questions, Guinea Pig?

471
00:45:48,600 --> 00:45:50,910
No, not until you stop acting suspicious.

472
00:45:51,660 --> 00:45:53,450
Follow me if you want to know.

473
00:45:55,800 --> 00:46:05,930
Quickly!

474
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:16,710
Hello, there.

475
00:46:16,710 --> 00:46:22,450
Go ahead and pick what you like. We have it from a thousand to ten thousand baht.

476
00:46:22,450 --> 00:46:25,710
Are you going to use it for delivery or exercising?

477
00:46:27,460 --> 00:46:28,880
Go and pick one.

478
00:46:30,060 --> 00:46:31,150
A bike?

479
00:46:31,660 --> 00:46:34,210
Mhm, do you think they’re oxcarts?

480
00:46:37,300 --> 00:46:39,380
It’s to replace the old one that I threw away.

481
00:46:39,380 --> 00:46:43,050
So that you won’t have another excuse to complain to my dad.

482
00:46:43,360 --> 00:46:44,860
I don’t want it.

483
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:49,280
What’s so different whether a father or a daughter pays for it?

484
00:46:49,330 --> 00:46:50,110
It is!

485
00:46:50,110 --> 00:46:53,710
Uncle might be rich but he is careful with his money and knows how to spend.

486
00:46:53,710 --> 00:46:56,750
But you, you threw away a bike that’s still in good condition.

487
00:46:56,750 --> 00:46:59,150
And you don’t even feel guilty about it.

488
00:47:00,500 --> 00:47:01,510
Are you done?

489
00:47:01,530 --> 00:47:04,380
Yes! And if that’s all you want from me, then I’m going back.

490
00:47:05,800 --> 00:47:06,380
Let me go.

491
00:47:06,680 --> 00:47:08,780
Or else you’ll get hurt.

492
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:10,410
Don’t make a fuss.

493
00:47:10,410 --> 00:47:11,980
If you want to go back, just go and pick one.

494
00:47:11,980 --> 00:47:13,380
It’s not like I want to be here.

495
00:47:13,400 --> 00:47:16,450
As if I begged you to take me here.

496
00:47:17,930 --> 00:47:20,150
Stop complaining and hurry up.

497
00:47:20,150 --> 00:47:23,050
I don’t want to stay close to you for even a minute–it’s annoying!

498
00:47:23,050 --> 00:47:24,680
You’re annoying too!

499
00:47:24,680 --> 00:47:26,280
You both are annoying!

500
00:47:28,210 --> 00:47:30,250
Are you going to buy it or not?

501
00:47:32,800 --> 00:47:33,600
So?

502
00:47:35,330 --> 00:47:36,310
Hurry up!

503
00:47:37,560 --> 00:47:38,880
So fussy.

504
00:47:46,930 --> 00:47:51,050
Why bother? It’s not like I want it.

505
00:47:51,060 --> 00:47:51,860
Thanks, girl.

506
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:54,110
Can you take it to the car for me?

507
00:47:54,380 --> 00:47:55,210
Sure.

508
00:47:57,930 --> 00:48:01,980
Saw! Come and take this bike to her car.

509
00:48:02,160 --> 00:48:03,150
Yes, Boss.

510
00:48:08,800 --> 00:48:10,480
That’s it.

511
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:18,460
So, do you want to go anywhere or buy anything else?

512
00:49:12,260 --> 00:49:15,310
Hey, are you done? You should have some manners.

513
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:18,550
Why the hell would you ask me if I wanted to buy anything?

514
00:49:18,550 --> 00:49:21,380
And look, I’m buying them for your office.

515
00:49:21,380 --> 00:49:23,580
If you don’t want to be here, go and wait in the car.

516
00:49:24,860 --> 00:49:26,950
I was just asking. What’s wrong with her?

517
00:49:27,250 --> 00:49:29,380
Does she have a hole in her mouth or what?

518
00:49:37,930 --> 00:49:41,980
‘Buffalo Fai, control freak’.

519
00:49:45,560 --> 00:49:49,850
‘Buffalo Fai, nasty mouth’

520
00:49:49,860 --> 00:49:54,110
‘Buffalo Fai, bloody Monkey’s Flea’.

521
00:49:57,530 --> 00:49:59,110
Did you just curse at me?

522
00:49:59,730 --> 00:50:03,980
No, just testing the pen. Don’t start it.

523
00:50:04,300 --> 00:50:07,350
But I saw you writing something. Let me see.

524
00:50:09,860 --> 00:50:10,660
Here, Granny.

525
00:50:11,530 --> 00:50:14,910
Hey, I’m done. Didn’t you say you want to hurry home?

526
00:50:18,060 --> 00:50:19,300
Did you write this for me?

527
00:50:23,330 --> 00:50:25,180
‘Stealing a glance at you’.

528
00:50:29,400 --> 00:50:31,110
What? I didn’t write that!

529
00:50:33,960 --> 00:50:35,250
That’s not mine.

530
00:50:37,730 --> 00:50:40,810
Auntie, I don’t want them anymore.

531
00:50:43,330 --> 00:50:46,210
Hey, what’s the rush? Don’t you want them anymore?

532
00:50:49,080 --> 00:50:51,510
[Humming] Stealing a glance at you…

533
00:50:54,930 --> 00:50:56,250
See you later, Granny.

534
00:51:17,700 --> 00:51:18,700
Is your butt growing roots?

535
00:51:19,200 --> 00:51:20,960
Why am I doing everything when I’m the one who paid for it?

536
00:51:21,760 --> 00:51:23,410
Who told you to buy it then?

537
00:51:24,930 --> 00:51:26,050
Young Master!

538
00:51:26,560 --> 00:51:31,680
Oh, wow! Your new bike is looking fabulous, Miss Kaphrao.

539
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:37,810
I bought it but it seems someone around here is being ungrateful.

540
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:42,280
The old one still works fine but someone lunatic just threw it away.

541
00:51:44,700 --> 00:51:47,780
Oh, actually, the old one was already worn out.

542
00:51:47,780 --> 00:51:51,350
Its chain often fell off. I tried to fix it many times but it didn’t work.

543
00:51:51,980 --> 00:51:56,510
Young Master thought it’d be dangerous if you kept using it, so she told Piak to throw it away.

544
00:52:14,700 --> 00:52:18,500
I was only afraid that if you fell off that bike, you might run to Dad and fake being a victim to get him on your side.

545
00:52:19,100 --> 00:52:21,400
That’s why I bought you a new one just to get it over with.

546
00:52:21,900 --> 00:52:23,410
You and your ugly thoughts!

547
00:52:23,600 --> 00:52:26,200
The Master wants both of you to eat with him at the main house.

548
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:29,210
He needs to talk to you about something.

549
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:39,810
Eat up, girls.

550
00:52:48,560 --> 00:52:53,810
Fai, you’ll attend the grand opening of Nam’s new resort, right?

551
00:52:54,210 --> 00:52:57,110
I want you to take Kaphrao with you too.

552
00:52:58,160 --> 00:53:01,260
What? Why should I take this Gremlin with me?

553
00:53:02,460 --> 00:53:08,180
Well, I want her to go see things and also get to know your siblings.

554
00:53:09,130 --> 00:53:12,450
Wake up, Dad. She’s not related to us.

555
00:53:12,450 --> 00:53:14,080
Why should she get to know my siblings?

556
00:53:14,100 --> 00:53:18,880
Isn’t it better to be acquainted? Who knows–we might find it useful in the future.

557
00:53:19,760 --> 00:53:23,250
But I don’t want to take her with me–it’s a burden!

558
00:53:23,400 --> 00:53:24,460
I don’t want to go with her either!

559
00:53:24,560 --> 00:53:25,810
Who said I’d take you with me?

560
00:53:25,860 --> 00:53:27,400
Uncle, please let me stay here to help you with work.

561
00:53:27,560 --> 00:53:29,100
All right, all right. Fine.

562
00:53:29,360 --> 00:53:33,480
If you don’t want to go, then let’s do that. I’m not gonna force you, okay?

563
00:53:33,500 --> 00:53:34,280
Thank you.

564
00:53:41,160 --> 00:53:46,150
While Fai is away, I’ll help coach you at work instead, is that good?

565
00:53:46,360 --> 00:53:47,350
That’s great.

566
00:53:48,460 --> 00:53:49,180
Eat up then.

567
00:53:49,180 --> 00:53:49,780
Yes.

568
00:53:54,160 --> 00:53:55,380
I’ve changed my mind.

569
00:53:56,730 --> 00:53:59,250
I’m going to take the Guinea Pig to Hua Hin with me.

570
00:53:59,930 --> 00:54:06,010
Hey, that’s all right. I won’t force you if you don’t want to do it.

571
00:54:06,860 --> 00:54:08,310
But I’m happy to do it.

572
00:54:09,660 --> 00:54:11,450
Good then, if you say so.

573
00:54:11,450 --> 00:54:15,310
Take her with you to Hua Hin too, okay?

574
00:54:15,500 --> 00:54:16,700
- Okay.
- Look after her too.

575
00:54:17,060 --> 00:54:18,130
I’ll take good care of her.

576
00:54:19,360 --> 00:54:21,180
Come, let’s eat then.

577
00:54:26,930 --> 00:54:31,510
The crispy omelette smells so good.

578
00:54:31,800 --> 00:54:33,680
Here, try it, Little One.

579
00:54:34,300 --> 00:54:35,160
I was about to try it.

580
00:54:36,360 --> 00:54:37,510
Thanks, Dad.

581
00:54:37,700 --> 00:54:38,500
You were?

582
00:54:39,200 --> 00:54:42,000
That’s fine. I’ll get you another one.

583
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:46,350
I want more.

584
00:54:48,360 --> 00:54:49,850
Fine, you want more.

585
00:54:50,330 --> 00:54:51,660
Take the whole plate then.

586
00:54:51,680 --> 00:54:52,500
Can I?

587
00:54:52,500 --> 00:54:54,710
Why not? Hey!

588
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:03,110
Really, you two.

589
00:55:07,360 --> 00:55:09,350
Have a safe trip, girls.

590
00:55:29,800 --> 00:55:31,660
[Next Episode]
Finally, what took you so long?

591
00:55:32,460 --> 00:55:34,180
Someone’s been dawdling.

592
00:55:34,330 --> 00:55:37,100
Are you two dating?

593
00:55:37,900 --> 00:55:38,750
No!

594
00:55:38,750 --> 00:55:42,180
I’d rather stay single for the rest of my life than have this Gremlin as my girlfriend.

595
00:55:42,860 --> 00:55:44,750
Isn’t she pretty, Fai?

596
00:55:45,200 --> 00:55:49,780
Yes–I mean, she’s okay but not that pretty.

597
00:55:50,100 --> 00:55:52,610
Phrao! Are you Kaphrao?

598
00:55:54,680 --> 00:55:56,950
Nod! Hey!

599
00:55:59,160 --> 00:56:02,710
Nod, stop it. Don’t make a scene.

600
00:56:02,930 --> 00:56:04,750
I’m tired. I want to go home now.

601
00:56:04,750 --> 00:56:07,380
Then, let’s go talk in your room after this.

602
00:56:07,400 --> 00:56:08,610
Okay, sure!

603
00:56:24,280 --> 00:56:31,310
♫I still remember vividly that day when we first met♫

604
00:56:31,880 --> 00:56:37,650
♫Those memories we had together never fade away from my heart♫

605
00:56:38,010 --> 00:56:45,610
♫We might never say it out loud how we feel for each other♫

606
00:56:45,610 --> 00:56:51,380
♫But deep down we both know how we feel♫

607
00:56:51,380 --> 00:56:57,510
♫Those things in the past, I still can’t forget them♫

608
00:56:57,510 --> 00:57:03,610
♫I want to know if you’re like that too–do you also feel the same?♫

609
00:57:04,010 --> 00:57:11,580
♫I could never forget those eyes of yours♫

610
00:57:11,580 --> 00:57:18,010
♫The warmth you used to give me, I still remember it vividly♫

611
00:57:18,310 --> 00:57:25,380
♫No matter for how long, you’ll always remain in my heart♫

612
00:57:25,380 --> 00:57:35,780
♫All those years I’ve been waiting, for us to finally be together again♫

613
00:57:43,810 --> 00:57:47,710
[North Star Entertainment]

614
00:57:47,710 --> 00:57:51,710
[Flaming Chains of Love]

